# Aipify Architecture Layers

See [AIPIFY_MASTER_STRUCTURE_BLUEPRINT.md](../../AIPIFY_MASTER_STRUCTURE_BLUEPRINT.md) (Phase 500) for the permanent five-layer hierarchy.

## Layer separation

| Layer | Who | Purpose |
|-------|-----|---------|
| **Super Admin** | Aipify Group AS internal | Platform governance — never expose customer business operations |
| **Platform Admin** | Aipify platform operators | Customer lifecycle, subscriptions, trust governance — not customer daily workflows |
| **Customer Portal** | Paying customer (`/app/*`) | Customer's business — never expose global platform operations |
| **Business Packs** | Customer Portal extensions | Operationally focused modules (e.g. Aipify Hosts) — same tenant isolation |
| **Companion** | Cross-surface guidance | Guidance only — never replaces ownership, never a separate product |

## Decision filter

Before every screen or feature, answer: **Who is this for?**

If unclear → pause and redesign. Do not mix Super Admin, Platform Admin, and Customer Portal concerns in one surface.

## Hosts modules (Business Pack)

- Feature owner: **CUSTOMER APP**
- Routes: `/app/aipify-hosts/*`
- Business logic: Supabase RPCs — panels are thin clients
- Distinct from Guest Intelligence (Phase 04) and Guest Center (Phase 15)
